      "content": "but it's more than just \"exploring\" though. the way it's happening in my house feels so specific, like it's tuned just to me. if they have the tech to detect these subtle shifts in my behavior or mood, wouldn't it be a huge advantage for them to run these kinds of tests on real people in real environments? like, wouldn't a company want to see how an algorithm actually performs when it's monitoring a live person?",
