    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "exactly. and if they are doing this, they aren't exactly going to ask for permission before running a live test on some random person's living room to see if their predictive models work. if the lights and thermostat are reacting to my stress levels in real-time, it feels like i'm basically part of an unconsented study. doesn't that mean my actual home is being used as a data collection lab for them?",
